{
  "name": "Inextinguishable Flame",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "type": "String",
      "label": "Description",
      "value": "<p>You make a normal fire inextinguishable by any means. The target can be up to the size of a campfire and remains burning for Willpower Bonus hours. The duration is extended to days with +2 SL on your Casting Test, weeks with +4 SL, and months with +6 SL.</p><p>The fire does not consume fuel while the spell lasts. Burning logs that are separated into smaller fires remain inextinguishable. Alternatively, you can cast this in reverse to extinguish any fire of the same size. No other spell can extinguish an Inextinguishable Flame, nor can its effect be dispelled.</p><p><strong>Lore:</strong> You may inflict +1 @Condition[Ablaze] Condition on anyone targeted by spells from the Lore of Fire, unless they also possess the Arcane Magic (Fire) Talent. Every Ablaze condition within Willpower Bonus yards adds +10 to attempts to Channel or Cast with Aqshy.</p><p></p>"
    },
